<li><a href="/scp-150">SCP-150</a>: An SCP about your body becoming something no longer yours. Co-authored with <a href="/dr-arvind-desais-personnel-file">A Random Day</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2091">SCP-2091</a>: An SCP about strong bonds between a bear and his granddaughter.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2110">SCP-2110</a>: An SCP about feeling safe.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2246">SCP-2246</a>: An SCP about a person who writes and writes.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2290">SCP-2290</a>: An SCP about abuse. Originally co-authored with and rewritten by <a href="/dr-cimmerian-s-personnel-file">Doctor Cimmerian</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2620">SCP-2620</a>: An SCP about a washing machine who is a food critic.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2906">SCP-2906</a>: An SCP about a Foundation-created cognitohazard and <a href="/anderson-robotics-hub">Anderson</a>'s take on it. Co-authored with <a href="/twistedgears-personnel-file">TwistedGears</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3015">SCP-3015</a>: An SCP about self-doubt and insecurity.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3090">SCP-3090</a>: An SCP about gaming when you're an objecthead. Originally written by and then co-authored with <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/th4nkyoub3n" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3079214); return false;">th4nkyoub3n</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3130">SCP-3130</a>: An SCP about feeling alone.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3290">SCP-3290</a>: An SCP about easy revenge.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3351">SCP-3351</a>: An SCP about the environment.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3412">SCP-3412</a>: An SCP about escaping.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-930-j">SCP-930-J</a>: An SCP about a little rascal, but hopefully you can babysit it for me?</li>
<li><a href="/scp-damej-j">SCP-damej-J</a> <strong>[EPILEPSY WARNING]</strong>: An SCP about a damej robit.</li>
</ul>
