<ul>
<li><a href="/so-it-was">So It Was</a>: A tale about <a href="/sandrewswann-s-proposal">S Andrew Swann's Proposal</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/leeway">Leeway</a>: A tale about <a href="/scp-2740">SCP-2740</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/anime-is-art-too-guys">Anime Is Art Too, Guys</a>: A tale about an anartist, rewritten for <a href="/cool-war-2-hub">Cool War 2: Ruiz From Your Grave</a> by DolphinSlugchugger.</li>
<li><a href="/all-of-me-wants-all-of-you">All of Me Wants All of You</a>: A tale about Rose Labelle, incorporating <a href="/scp-2277">SCP-2277</a> a little bit. Song title comes from a <a href="http://youtube.com/watch?v=Se6-q57xJCg">Sufjan Stevens</a> song.</li>
<li><a href="/i-forget-myself-in-this-wondrous-night">I Forget Myself in This Wondrous Night</a>: A tale about <a href="/scp-1467">SCP-1467</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/and-then-i-died3">And Then I Died... Part III</a>: A collaborative game that is on hiatus.</li>
<li><a href="/my-beloved-gecko">My Beloved Gecko</a>: A tale about Dr. Gears and <a href="/scp-682">SCP-682</a>, written for the <a href="/an-incredibly-important-announcement">Crack Fiction Contest</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/primae-formae">Prelude: Primae Formae</a>: A tale about the beginnings of the <a href="/on-mount-golgotha-hub">On Mount Golgotha</a> canon.</li>
<li><a href="/gamers-against-weed-dossier">Gamers Against Weed Dossier</a>: A tale that's more like the Foundation's dossier on Gamers Against Weed.</li>
<li><a href="/wriggle-like-a-fucking-eel">Wriggle Like a Fucking Eel</a>: A tale about an evil man.</li>
<li><a href="/the-skylarking-gala">The Skylarking Gala</a>: A GoI Format about AWCY? throwing some concerts.</li>
<li><a href="/charles-ogden-gears">Intro - Note: Charles Ogden Gears</a>: A GoI Format about Dr. Gears by Nobody. The first of a tale series.</li>
<li><a href="/like-clockwork-hub">...Like Clockwork Hub</a>: A tale series about Researcher Talloran's struggle with <a href="/scp-3999">SCP-3999</a>. To, well, to put its themes real mildly.</li>
<li><a href="/it-feels-like-being-weightless">What Do You Think Love Feels Like Once You Understand It?</a>: A tale about <a href="/scp-2240">SCP-2240</a> reflecting on love.</li>
<li><a href="/misfire-hub">Misfire Hub</a>: A tale series about unfortunate murders. Mostly takes place over the course of one day. Written for the <a href="/72-hour-jam-contest">72 Hour Jam Contest</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/i-want-to-dream">&quot;I'm dying.&quot; &quot;Is it blissful?&quot;</a>: A tale about Glass's incredulous session with Kondraki, written for the <a href="/siabhub">Ship in a Bottle</a> canon.</li>
<li><a href="/danger-in-the-manger">You Ain't No Family</a>: A tale about friends and family.</li>
<li><a class="newpage" href="/how-to-leave-town-hub">How to Leave Town</a>: A tale series about artists, relationships, mental illness, and weed.</li>
<li><a href="/and-have-fun">Cheers, Kiddo!</a>: A tale about memory and that which you cannot remember cleanly, written for the <a href="/cliche-con-2019">Cliché-Con 2019</a> contest.</li>
<li><a href="/potato-girl">Potato Girl</a>: A tale about Heather's Halloween. Written for the <a href="/144-hour-jam-contest">144-Hour Jam Contest</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/super-stars">Super Stars!</a>: A tale about anomalous friends in the desert. Written for <a href="/learning-the-alphabet-hub">Learning the Alphabet</a>.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
